#. type: Title ===
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:3
#, no-wrap
msgid "First Login Flow"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:8
#, no-wrap
msgid "When a user logs in through identity brokering some aspects of the user are imported and linked within the realm's local database.\n"
"When {project_name} successfully authenticates users through an external identity provider\n"
"there can be two situations:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "There is already a {project_name} user account imported and linked with the authenticated identity provider account.\n"
"In this case, {project_name} will just authenticate as the existing user and redirect back to application.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "There is not yet an existing {project_name} user account imported and linked for this external user.\n"
"Usually you just want to register and import the new account into {project_name} database, but what if there is an existing\n"
"{project_name} account with the same email? Automatically linking the existing local account to the external\n"
"identity provider is a potential security hole as you can't always trust the information you get from the external identity provider.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "Different organizations have different requirements when dealing with some of the conflicts and situations listed above.\n"
"For this, there is a `First Login Flow` option in the IDP settings which allows you to choose a <<_authentication-flows, workflow>> that will be\n"
"used after a user logs in from an external IDP the first time.\n"
"By default it points to `first broker login` flow, but you can configure and use your own flow and use different flows for different identity providers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:24
#, no-wrap
msgid "The flow itself is configured in admin console under `Authentication` tab.\n"
"When you choose `First Broker Login` flow, you will see what authenticators are used by default.\n"
"You can re-configure the existing flow. (For example you can disable some authenticators, mark some of them as `required`, configure some authenticators, etc).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "ifeval::[{project_community}==true]\n"
"You can also create a new authentication flow and/or write your own Authenticator implementations and use it in your flow.\n"
"See link:{developerguide_link}[{developerguide_name}] for more details.\n"
"endif::[]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:30
#, no-wrap
msgid "Default First Login Flow"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "Let's describe the default behaviour provided by `First Broker Login` flow.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "Review Profile"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "This authenticator might display the profile info page, where the user can review his profile retrieved from an identity provider.\n"
"The authenticator is configurable.\n"
"You can set the `Update Profile On First Login` option.\n"
"When `On`, users will be always presented with the profile page asking for additional information in order to federate their identities.\n"
"When `missing`, users will be presented with the profile page only if some mandatory information (email, first name, last name) is not provided by the identity provider.\n"
"If `Off`, the profile page won't be displayed, unless user clicks in later phase on `Review profile info` link (page displayed in later phase\n"
"by `Confirm Link Existing Account` authenticator)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:43
#, no-wrap
msgid "Create User If Unique"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "This authenticator checks if there is already an existing {project_name} account with same email or username like the account from the identity provider.\n"
"If it's not, then the authenticator just creates a new local {project_name} account and links it with the identity provider and the whole flow is finished.\n"
"Otherwise it goes to the next `Handle Existing Account` subflow.\n"
"If you always want to ensure that there is no duplicated account, you can mark this authenticator as `REQUIRED` . In this case, the user\n"
"will see the error page if there is existing {project_name} account and the user will need to link his identity provider account through Account management.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "Confirm Link Existing Account"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "On the info page, the user will see that there is an existing {project_name} account with same email.\n"
"He can review his profile again and use different email or username (flow is restarted and goes back to `Review Profile` authenticator).\n"
"Or he can confirm that he wants to link the identity provider account with his existing {project_name} account.\n"
"Disable this authenticator if you don't want users to see this confirmation page, but go straight to linking identity provider account by email verification or re-authentication.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verify Existing Account By Email"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "This authenticator is `ALTERNATIVE` by default, so it's used only if the realm has SMTP setup configured.\n"
"It will send mail to the user, where he can confirm that he wants to link the identity provider with his {project_name} account.\n"
"Disable this if you don't want to confirm linking by email, but instead you always want users to reauthenticate with their password (and alternatively OTP).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Labeled list
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "Verify Existing Account By Re-authentication"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: source/server_admin/topics/identity-broker/first-login-flow.adoc:66
#, no-wrap
msgid "This authenticator is used if email authenticator is disabled or non-available (SMTP not configured for realm). It will display a login screen\n"
"where the user needs to authenticate with his password to link his {project_name} account with the Identity provider.\n"
"User can also re-authenticate with some different identity provider, which is already linked to his {project_name} account.\n"
"You can also force users to use OTP. Otherwise it's optional and used only if OTP is already set for the user account.\n"
msgstr ""

